{
  "texts": [
    "Control experiments confirmed that the second eye-blink was coupled to the first, and not to the original cue.",
    "Moreover, on many trials, the rabbits showed a third and even fourth eye-blink.",
    "This is because feedback signals from the first, second, or third blink were the same.",
    "Thus, the feedback signals from the first blink triggered the second blink, feedback from the second triggered the third, and so forth.",
    "Rabbits could also learn to use a blink of the left eye as a cue for a blink of the right eye."
  ]
}